{"word":"Διόσκουροι","slug":"Διόσκουροι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Διόσϰουροι, ων, οἱ</el></b> [later form of <el>Διόσϰουρος</el>: <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Διός\">Διός</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:κόρος\">κόρος</a></el> ‘son’] <b><i>the Dioscuri,</i></b> epithet of Castor and Pollux, twin sons of Zeus and Leda, and dear to mariners <b><a href='B:510 28:11'>Ac 28:11</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Διός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:διότι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}